A cocktail party was held on Monday onboard one of the three Japanese vessels that had docked in Mombasa carrying 750 officers.JS Kashima, JS Setoyuki and JS Asagiri are under the command of Rear Admiral Hidetoshi Iwasaki.During, the cocktail, Japanese ambassador Toshitsugu Uesawa welcomed the navy officers to Kenya and called for a strong bilateral relationship in the fight against piracy.The fleet, at sea for four months now, has been to France, Italy, Panama, US, UK, Belgium, Lithuania, Germany, Malta and Djibouti. Among those present at the cocktail included Mombasa education executive Tendai Lewa, Kenya Navy deputy commander-in-chief Brigadier Charles Khariri and former Technical University of Mombasa vice-chancellor Professor Josphat Mwatela.